        get the single stock with the primary key given by all the parameters
        Parameters:
        project - the given project
        timeStamp - the given timeStamp

        useValue - the name of the use value of this stock, as a String
        stockType - the type of this stock (money, productive, sales, consumption) as a String
        Returns:
        the single stock defined by this primary key, null if it does not exist

      • switchProjects

        public static void switchProjects(int newProjectID,
                                  ActionButtonsBox actionButtonsBox)
        Switch from one project to another.

        (1)copy the current timeStamp and timeStampDisplayCursor into the current Project record

        (2)retrieve the timeStamp and timeStampDisplayCursor from the new Project

        (4)save the current Project record to the database

        (3)set 'currentProject' to be the new project

        (4)the calling method must refresh the display

        Parameters:
        newProjectID - the ID of the project to switch to
        actionButtonsBox - the actionButtonsBox which has invoked the switch (and which knows the buttonState of the current project)
